quran[37]{c,v,t}:
  19,22,So she conceived him and then withdrew with him to a remote place
  19,23,"And the throes of childbirth drove her to the trunk of a palm tree. She said, \"Oh, would that I had died before this, and had been a thing long forgotten"
  19,24,"Then a voice called out to her from beneath her, \"Grieve not, your Lord has surely made a canal flow beneath you"
  19,25,And shake the trunk of the palm tree towards you. It will drop on you fresh ripe dates
  19,26,"So eat and drink and relax! Then if you should see any man, tell him (by signs), \"I have indeed vowed unto the Gracious Allah not to speak to any man today"
  19,27,"And she came to her people carrying the child. They said, \"O Mary! You have verily done a terrible thing"
  19,28,"O sister of Aaron ! Your father was not a bad man, nor was your mother an unchaste woman"
  19,29,"But she pointed to him. They said, \"How could we speak to a mere child in cradle"
  19,30,"The child said, \"I am indeed a devotee of Allah. HE has given me the Book and made me a Prophet"
  19,31,"And He has made me blessed wherever I may be, and He has enjoined on me prayer and charity so long as I live"
  19,32,"And to be couteous to my mother. And He has not made me insolent, impudent"
  19,33,"And peace on me on the day I was born, the day I die and the day I am raised to life again"
  19,34,"This (as narrated in Verses to above) then is Jesus, son of Mary — the word of Truth about which they raise disputes"
  19,35,"It is not befitting the majesty of Allah that He should beget a son. Glorified He is! When He has decreed a matter, He only says to it \"Be,\" and it is"
  19,36,"And, indeed, Allah is my Lord and your Lord; hence, worship Him. This is the Straight Path"
  19,37,But the tribes disagreed among themselves — and woe to those who disbelieve — about the Court of Judgment to be assembled on a tremendous Day
  19,38,"Make them listen to you when you speak to them about the Day they shall appear before Us, and make them understand the significance of that Day. But those who are wicked shall continue to remain grossly mistaken about the Day"
  19,39,"And warn them of the Day of intense regret, when all matters get finally decided. And they are under a delusion and they do not believe"
  19,40,"We do indeed inherit the earth and all those who are on it, and to Us they all shall be returned"
  19,41,And make mention of Abraham in the Book. He was indeed a true Prophet
  19,42,"When he said to his father, \"O my father! Why do you worship a thing that neither hears nor sees, nor does it give you any benefit whatsoever"
  19,43,O my father! I do have some knowledge that you do not. So follow me! I will show you the Right Path
  19,44,"O my father! Worship not the Satan. The Satan is indeed a rebel against Allah, the Gracious"
  19,45,"O my father! I am afraid, a punishment from the Gracious Allah may afflict you and you may befriend the Satan"
  19,46,"He (Abraham's father) said, \"Are you averse to my gods, O Abraham? If you do not desist I will certainly pelt you with stones. And leave me alone for now"
  19,47,"Abraham said, \"Peace on you! I will pray to my Lord to forgive you. He is indeed ever benevolent to me"
  19,48,"And I will go away from you and what you pray to besides Allah, and I will pray to my Lord; may be my prayer to my Lord shall not remain unanswered"
  19,49,"So when he had gone away from them and what they worshipped besides Allah, We bestowed upon him Isaac and Jacob, and We made each a Prophet"
  19,50,"And We bestowed upon them Our mercy, and We gave them each a highly truthful tongue"
  19,51,And mention Moses in the Book. He was indeed pure and clean; and he was a Messenger Prophet
  19,52,"And We called to him from the right side of Mount Sinai, and We drew him near for a talk"
  19,53,"And We made for him, by Our mercy, his brother Aaron a Prophet"
  19,54,"And mention Ishmael in the Book. He was indeed true to his word, and a Messenger Prophet"
  19,55,"And he used to enjoin his family to pray and to give in charity, and his Lord was well pleased with him"
  19,56,And mention Idris in the Book. He was indeed a true Prophet
  19,57,And We raised him high in status
  19,58,"Those were men on whom Allah bestowed favours. Those were from among the Prophets of the seed of Adam, and of those whom We carried in the Ark with Noah, and of the seed of Abraham and Israel, and of those whom We guided and chose. Whenever Verses/signs of the Gracious Allah were recited to them, they would fall down prostrating and weeping"